result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher L. Lanier was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Christopher L. Lanier in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls  @ 10:30 am.  State gives plea agreement, Amended information filed, ct's 1 & 4 DRI, ct 2 Poss of Drug Paraph, misdemeanor, ct 3 Poss of Drg Paraph, plea and withheld sentence 18 months probation on each ct, concurrent, AODA and follow through, and costs.  Recess @ 10:32 am. Reconvene @ 10:38 am. Issues are resolved, State gives modification to sentence recommendation 12 months probation.  Atty Laufenberg and def. agree with plea agreement modified.  Plea questionnaire and waiver of rights filed.  Def. understands charges and penalties.  Court will grant amendment in ct 2 Poss of Drg Paraph 961.573(1), no contest Ct 3 as charged, no contest.  DRI Ct's 1 & 4.  Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights. Def. understands elements.  Atty Laufenberg is satisfied.  Court finds pleas are freely & voluntarily given.  State and defense agree with factual basis.  Court finds factual basis, accepts plea and finds def. Guilty to Poss of Drg Paraph in Ct's 2 & 3.  State gives sentencing recommendation.  Atty Laufenberg gives sentencing recommendation.  Def. has nothing to say.  Court orders on ct 2 withheld jail sentence 12 months probation, AODA and complete any counseling deemed by agent, costs, $200 DNA Surcharge
Ct 3 withheld sentence 12 months probation, AODA and costs, 200 DNA Surcharge.  State heard on bond forfeiture.  Atty Laufenberg gives statement. Def. makes statement.  Court will not forfeit bond and gives reason.  Bond applied to costs. If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Court advised def. of firearm.  DNA Sample.  Def. advised of postconviction rights.
